[SN]TITLE[SN]
Macclesfield Town 0-2 Aldershot Town

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Aldershot moved into the National League play-off places with a comfortable win at Macclesfield.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Second-half goals from Kundai Benyu and Matt McClure earned the visitors a third straight victory.
The Shots edged a tight first period, with Benyu firing the best chance of the half over the bar in the 13th minute.
Macclesfield midfielder Kingsley James saw his half-volley easily saved by Jake Cole after the interval, while Rhys Browne headed a good chance over.
The hosts were made to pay for the wasted chances in the 59th minute when Benyu ran on to Bernard Mensah's pass to fire past Scott Flinders.
Macclesfield rallied in the final 10 minutes but the Shots sealed victory late on as McClure converted a rebound.
